    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A pattern of crackle in paintings occurring after all layers have dried, often penetrating the ground as well, resulting from subtle movements in the support, such as from changes of temperature or humidity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un modelo de craquelado en pintura, que ocurre después de que todas las capas se han secado, a menudo penetrando a la base, resultado de movimientos sutiles en el soporte así como de cambio de temperatura o humedad.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een craquelé-patroon in schilderijen dat dikwijls ook in de grondverf trekt, en ontstaat nadat alle lagen zijn opgedroogd als gevolg van nauwelijks merkbare bewegingen in de ondergrond, door bijvoorbeeld temperatuurveranderingen of vocht.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052378/Winkler Prins Encyclopedie (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>顏料層乾燥後出現於畫作表面的裂紋圖案，通常也會透入底材，任何底材的輕微變動，諸如溫度或濕度的變化，都會形成裂紋。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
